The paper deals with adversarial machine learning, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on game-theoretic formulations and randomized strategies suggests that the paper is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of handwritten digit recognition and spam/malware detection as application examples suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-fields such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
